k: while it mentions review-agent round, the behavior requires freshness/execution evidence, not LLM output quality; therefore Agentic/Workflow are not required. No real OS/network/subprocess requirement, so not System. Rejection gate: higher levels are disqualified by absence of any behavior text about evaluating model-generated content correctness.","test_description":"Create an initial round on diff D1, apply Phase 4 fixes producing diff D2, then attempt finalize PASS without running a new round -> must fail. Next record execution of a new round tied to D2 and re-run finalize -> allowed (subject to findings). Assert gate keys on round freshness against updated diff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings, the flow emits an escalation outcome instead of PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Pass 1: Integration, because this is end-of-loop policy using persisted findings plus round-counter state across modules. Pass 2 downgrade check: Unit would miss interaction bugs between round tracking and findings resolution status. Upgrade check: no explicit need for real external infra, no requirement to assess model-output quality, and no required multi-agent output chain for correctness of this rule. Integration-brake confirms no trigger for System/Agentic/Workflow.","test_description":"Simulate loop state at max rounds with at least one unresolved MUST-FIX finding in storage. Execute final decision path and assert emitted outcome is escalation (with PASS explicitly disallowed). Also verify PASS is emitted only when MUST-FIX set is empty before exhaustion.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.06}}]}
